column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luxtreme 28"
column6: I was looking for yoga pants that were high waisted, as I also bought the Seek the Heat bodysuit which I read needs to be paired with a high waisted pant. However, while the waistband may be comfortable it doesn't stay "high" while working through flows and I don't get the hugged sensation the description suggests. Overall, they're great for athleisure wearing, but I would search for a different legging if you're hoping for a high rise pant that stays high and that you don't have to worry about while working out.

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luxtreme 28"
column5: Leggings Get Looser With Every Wash
column6: I have been an avid wearer of wunder under high rise leggings since 2015. I bought a new pair a few weeks ago, and these leggings are no longer made like they used to be. After 3 washes, my new pair of Wunder Under's have loosened around the waist, crotch, and knees. I am constantly having to pull this pair up and always have a saggy behind. I bought the same size I have been wearing since 2015 so I am left to conclude that these are simply not made like they used to be. It's a shame this brand is still having quality assurance issues. Size 2 sizes down with these leggings if you want them to actually fit correctly.

column6: So obsessed with these. I own 3 pairs in different colors (and want more!). column6: I have other Lululemon leggings that fit me like a glove and I love them. It’s been about 2 years since I bought them and they still look like new. I just bought these in navy to freshen up my wardrobe. I bought the same size, and even double checked the size chart and took measurements just to be sure. When they arrived, I tried them on and they seemed a tad big, but I thought maybe if I washed them they might shrink a little. Wrong! I just wore them for the second time and the waist creeps down during the day, along with a droopy crotch. All around an unflattering look which is not what I expected based on my previous purchases. Now that they have been washed twice, I guess I’m stuck with them according to their return policy. Anyway, I would suggest sizing down on these leggings.

The overall fit is nice, they hug my legs and butt in a very flattering way. The fabric really is like wearing nothing and when I bend over, they remain opaque. An added bonus is that they don't attract pet hair because of the material, which was a huge selling point for me since I have a white dog who sheds a lot.
Yet, and this is kind've a deal breaker for me on a pair of high-rise leggings... the waistband absolutely will not stay up. It's very unflattering and annoying both while working out and daily wear and a big disappointment as I got high-rise with the intention of feeling more comfortable wearing crop tops.

column6: I was so excited to FINALLY order some Lululemon leggings, I've been hearing about them for years but wasn't sure I wanted to make the investment. Wanted to leave this review so that I could suggest that you try them on in the store instead of purchasing online like I did, to make sure that they fit. On a good note, they are comfortable, I just couldn't keep them up! :) BTW, I'm 5.9 and sometimes it's hard to find leggings long enough and these are plenty long enough, loved that.

I don't have a problem with the waist rolling down as other people have. They would probably work for low intensity workouts, but I wouldn't wear them for high intensity workouts. I wear a size 6 in jeans, but I buy a size 8 in all of my Lulu leggings, I don't like anything cutting into my waist. I could probably size down to a 6 as it is a high waist without a seam, but I'm not sure how it would feel on my thighs.

column6: I have always adored all of my past lululemon leggings. Their unmatched quality and durability were enough for me to justify their price tags. With this item, however, I was surprised to find none of the things that I liked about my other pairs. I went in looking for the Olive Green color in my favorite pair (All the right places) but they were completely sold out so I decided to go with these in Olive Green instead. I don't know what happened, but the high rise for some reason, didn't seem high enough like my other wunder unders were. The legs and ankle areas were choking and leaving marks on my skin. The waist band was constantly rolling down and creating a horrifying muffin top effect that was visible through my sweater. And don't even get me started on the prominence of camel-toe. These didn't feel "breathable" like all my other ones. I was told to go a size down from my other leggings because these were supposed to feel a bit more relaxed. They feel like the opposite. Maybe that was where it went wrong. Maybe it was the Luxtreme material being in this style? I have no idea. I am confused and need answers.

These pants specifically are wonderful for hot yoga. I've also got a pair of the... I think WunderUnder... leggings that have a thicker material. The material on this pair is thinner AND passes the bend-over test! Yas queen!
The pattern is so much fun and easier to match tops to than I thought. Black, blue, red, purple, pink all look great with these. I've gotten so many compliments on them! Also, they hide sweat really well, so they're seriously my favorite hot yoga pants. No more sweat-that-looks-like-pee spots! Yay! Highly recommend.

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luxtreme 28"
column6: Love the WunderUnder line, but these are definitely more snug than most of the other fabric combos. Its less likely to roll down during yoga (woo!), but it's also more likely to make you cranky if you happen to wear them for a couple hours (or are just bloated that particular day!). These are the ones I wear when all the others are in the wash. All in all, good pants, but not my fave.

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luxtreme 28"
column6: This was my first pair of Lululemon leggings and I was pretty excited to give them a try. They fit well, albeit a little long, although most leggings are as I am 5'1" and athletically petite. They were comfortable and flattering and I really liked the sage color and waist height. The first time I wore them, it was just for lounging and some light climbing, and they worked great. Then I took them for a lifting workout. I lift early in the morning and generally save cardio or higher intensity workouts for the evening, so that I don't sweat too much and don't have to shower before work. However, there is still a little sweating that inevitably happens in areas that are not particularly flattering. These pants showed ALL of my sweat. I don't know if it's particular to the sage color (I imagine black would be much less evident) or the material. But it was definitely a bit embarrassing, although in a self-deprecating manner pretty funny, and had I known that was going to happen I would have chosen to wear different pants that show sweat a bit more subtly . I will definitely be saving these for solo yoga sessions in my house, and lounging around rather than working out in public! I will also definitely buy black or another dark color for my next pair.

I did this and ended up purchasing these Wonder Under leggings instead. The sales rep that sold these to me said that they were much more durable than the align II leggings. This much is true, I have very minimal pilling with these (even though I think there should be no pilling if you pay so much $$ on them) however, my main complaint with these is that they fall down like crazy! The last thing you want to do while working out is have to tug on your pants. Very annoying! They get stretched out very quickly while wearing them. These leggings are also not butter soft like the others. They feel like typical work out spandex (nothing special).
All in all, these might be OK pants if I went a size smaller. But what the heck is up with lulu's quality?? I thought this was a high end brand, but the leggings wash up like bargain bin leggings. I would recommend not wasting money on this cheap garbage and take your business else where (like Athleta!!)

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luxtreme 28"
column6: I just recently bought my second pair after having my first pair for almost a year and a half. I bought the first pair in a size eight, don't get me wrong, I love these pants and they did fit great, but its either they stretched out from wear or I lost weight. I'm thinking the former. As I walk in them (after one or two wears) I have to pull them up almost every minute, thats why after a year I started to throw them in the dryer after I wash them, hoping they would shrink. However, I wear these only to lounge in and to go to school, so I am not worried about them sliding down while working out. But because they are stretched out and I have to constantly yank them up, I bought a six like my previous crops that I bought. So far, so good. They are not too tight and have been holding up fairly well. My black pair is my absolute go-to pair of lulu's and my new pair in the color "city lights multi black" I'm sure will become my new favorite! Another great thing about these leggings is that I have yet to have any pilling in the inner thigh area -- unlike my three month old athleta leggings. If you are worried about the length being too short (if you're tall) -- don't. I am 5'10" with super long legs and there is a small amount of extra fabric at the bottom of the pants. The only reason I give this 4/5 stars is because of the stretching out, otherwise these are amazing pants!

“Full-On® Luxtreme fabric's interlock construction offers great support and coverage with a cool, smooth feel” yup cool and smooth, kind of silky, nice.
“added Lycra® fibre for stretch and shape retention” no problem with stretching out, pilling or loose seams. Looks great after one month.
“waistband lies flat against your skin and won't dig in” Ha, great until I work out. No problem walking around, standing and sitting. I purchased 2 pairs 4 weeks ago, I’ve been to 4 yoga and 9 Pilates classes. Why am I the only one yanking on my pants trying to keep them up? Glad I also purchased a couple Cool Racerback II tops they are long and cover me enough so I’m not exposing myself between exercises.
“waistband pocket holds your key or card” love it
“Hugged Sensation” as advertised
“designed for: yoga, trainin” yup, that’s what i’m doing besides constantly pulling my pants up
I want to love them but I can’t. Did I buy the wrong size? Should I have gone smaller? The sales person in the store said they fit correctly. Not sure if I want to spend another hundred dollars just to experiment on another pair.

column5: Was hoping they'd live up to hype
column6:
I saw the new Fluorolace Multi in a photo of a Define jacket and I was like, I've gotta have those! Well, they arrived today and as with MANY (read, all) Lulu Full-On Luxtreme tights, they use the lightest possible color lining the inside of the fabric, and on these it's white. WHITE!! Why does Lululemon insist on doing this? 1. it makes it fade over parts of your body where they're might me more stretch, hips, thighs, butt, etc.
2. it makes it more see-through.
These are too busy to be see through and I was sure to try them on with bright striped underwear to test them out. But, because I have big thighs they fade and stretch and the pattern just doesn't look good. Oddly it doesn't do this over my butt and I have a sizable one. For ref, 34" waist 45.5" hips and I usually wear 8 or 10 in this particular fabric, but on these the waist was too big and even just looking in different mirrors, I had to keep pulling them up. They are going back. Also, the rise is like the photo, it's really not that high, at least not in the front.
Dear Lulu: Please line your pants with the darkest color of the fabric's pattern rather than white, or the lightest. It would really make a big difference in terms of fade and issues with your products being see-through. Thank you!

column6:
I love lululemon. I am a die-hard lululemon.... or, I was. I own many different types of their leggings and finally got my hands on the Wunder Unders. Can you say, embarrassingly shear and see through??? No, I am not saying that when I squat they go shear--I am saying that if you move even slightly (walking, for instance) everyone is going to see your little bum AND the exact fabric of the VS panties you are wearing.... from the FRONT. No, I am not exaggerating. Even my cheap little HM leggings aren't shear in the front! Imagine my horrified little face when I get to the well-lit locker room of my gym at 6 am and realize that everyone and their cute little mom is going to be able to see that I am festive as HECK and wearing white no show underwear with cute little silver snowflakes on them. These are the nightmares of legging-wearers everywhere. Come on, Lululemon, you can do better than this.
I will add: these leggings do have good tummy control and are a soft fabric, but that is to be expected when buying $100 leggings from Lululemon. Just like how I expect with Lululemon leggings, I should be able to walk in these leggings and not have the whole world see my cute little Christmas panties. *Insert crying emoji here*

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luxtreme 28"
column6: These tights are great! Love the material feeling, like butter. I will note that they are slightly see-through. I'm 5'6, 140, and got my usual size 6. I tried both the 6 and 8 on in the store. The 6 does stretch the pattern around my thighs and bum in a way that the black becomes sheer, but the 8 was far to loose at the high waist. The sales associate also mentioned they become more stretchy as you sweat and would most likely roll down if I bought them too big. Glad I went with the 6, they do feel great, even as I get sweaty, and maintain enough compression to not be bothered with dreaded roll down/pull up needs. Just know that if you're very bothered by see-through, wear a nude panty or thong!

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luxtreme 28"
column6: I've had these tights for a few months but they have pilled pretty quickly. I always follow the washing instructions and don't wear them that often. They also stretch out after one wash and then I have to re wash them to get them back to their original shape. They are a nice fabric but I just hoped they would stay in better condition longer because they are so dang expensive :(

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luxtreme 28"
column6: Let me say something about these pants... I LOVE THEM! I have a few pairs and am getting more. I love the patterns and the way the full on luxtreme feels... So comfortable and true to size! Fits true to size, I am a size 4 and 5'7 130lbs. These pants are so great to just hang around the house in or go to class (I'm in college). I also LOVE wearing them to the gym for weightlifting or any kind of HIIT! Stitching has not come undone and I have had mine since March and wear them frequently. If you was your lulu clothing PROPERLY you will not have issues! Wash with the same materials (athletic material) and only air dry! Don't use a detergent with built in fabric softener. So sick of seeing people complain about lulu things being "bad quality" when they most likely don't wash them correctly. Also, if you wear something a lot over a year or so it WILL wear out, no matter what kind of quality. Make more patterns please, love love love this pant!

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luxtreme 28"
column6: Theses were my first pair of lulus, i remember my 8th grade year all my friends would have 8 pairs and i would really feel left out, and they took care of them. Since i knew that they were nice leggings i obviously coped a pair (for people that don't know what coped is its decided to buy it.) I see a lot of people that write reviews say that the pilling comes undone etc, but im not sure if you guys know how to wash them (not to be rude...) at least my friends kept them in good shape for a long time, but anyways you wash them by themselves in the washer and then let them air dry, that way nothing clings onto anything and there isn't pilling, i thought i would share :)

column5: Great fit at first... but two months later.. now loose!!
column6: I have a few pairs of wunder under luxtreme high rise pants and they never failed to disappoint.. so when I was looking for black basic tights, WUs were the the first thing I looked at. In the store, and during the first few times I wore them, they were great. They fit well, had the hugged-in sensation, and looked great. But lately, merely two months after i got them from the store, they seem to stretch out after the first hour of wear. By the time i get to the end of my yoga class or dance class/rehearsal, they are sliding and sagging at the butt/crotch and I find myself adjusting and pulling the pants up. I've never had such problems with my other luxtreme pants and shorts, so i'm wondering if something's up with this particular black fabric! It was quite a disapointment as I have had good experiences with WU pants previously.. and with that price tag, I expected my black pants to last at least two years rather than two months...

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luxtreme 28"
column5: Heavenly, too good to be true pants
column6: I don't often feel compelled to write reviews- BUT! I feel the need to share my experience with these pants. I bought my first pair shortly after having baby #2 in a size 8. They fit amazingly through my whole postpartum weight loss journey (I was about 170 lbs when I bought them and got down to 130 lbs.) Now, almost 2 years later, I am 5 1/2 months pregnant with baby #3 and am still wearing this same pair of pants regularly! How in the world can something fit so perfectly over a range of 40+ pounds, and pregnant or not pregnant?! They feel super supportive, they show off my curves in the most flattering way, and they have held up nearly perfectly despite my constant use. I own pants from Nike and Under Armour and nothing I've tried compare to these. I jog, lift weights, do HIIT, you name it, and they have never slid down or moved, even at my lowest weight. Incredible, heaven-sent pants that make my confidence sore at any size. I will definitely purchase again and again. As much as I'd love to try other Lulu pants, I feel like I've already found perfection with these and why mess that up. Haha!

column6: All I asked for this year for my birthday from family was Lululemon Gift Cards since I could never bring myself to spend the money, but noticed how great they looked on everyone else. I went with basic and black, and did enjoy the look of the high rise, however during any kind of workouts including yoga, they ride down significantly. The fit is right in terms of size, but the hi rise waist does not seem to stay in place with the slightest of movement. After 1 month and approximately 3 cold washes, I noticed not only did the fade, but also began to have piling like crazy, which I'm now seeing many people experienced. I'm now on month 2, and I have never dried these pants, only air-dryed, and still the quality has gone downhill fast. It's super disappointed when you can spend $25-30 on a pair from TJ Maxx or Marshalls and they hold up better than a pair for $98! I'm afraid to wear them to their house, because all I did was go on and on about how great they were before I bought them, and they thought the price was outrageous. I've never really been a big review kind of person, but if your like me and contemplating the money, I say save it or invest it in 3-4 cheaper pairs.

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luxtreme 28"
column5: I love these, despite scary reviews. ;)
column6:
Sometimes I read reviews on here and am curious what expectations people have.... I've only recently started buying lulu pants, I have a lot of bras and one day I saw a print in the Wunder Under Full on Luxtreme in an e-mail and had to go check it out. I tried them on and FELL IN LOVE. These pants are AMAZING, they are tight, secure, and make me feel slim. The waistband is the perfect tightness; keeps the tum in but doesn't cut off my circulation. I love LOOOVE how fast these dry when I take a hot yoga class or just get really sweaty in a spin class. I wash in cold and lay out to dry. I've seen slight pilling but I also have thick thighs that rub so I'm never too shocked when I see pilling.
The only con is they do start to stretch out if I wear them too often / for a full day of non athletic activities. I sometimes wonder if I should have sized down. Also they sometimes fall down when I'm running, but seem to stay/secure to my body once I start sweating a little / my body temp rises.
For reference, I am 5'4" and 155lbs and wear a size 8-10 in jeans, and my Wunder Unders are a size 8.. I could possibly size down but the 8's are fine.

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luxtreme 28"
column5: Poor, negative customer service in-store, and quality issues...again
column6:
I had previously left a positive review for the WUP high waist null, but I can't amend my review to reflect the poor quality and poor customer service that has since ensued. So here's my amended review.
I purchased these pants on March 14, 2017. Initially I liked them although 20 minutes or so into my workout they would bag at the knees and crotch (I tried a size down and they were sheer, so I stuck to my regular size). I liked the pattern, so I stuck with them even though I always reach for my tight stuff and fast & frees over them.
I went to put them on and noticed two small snags near the crotch, one of which was actually a pin-sized hole. If I could upload a photo I would, but it is obvious from the in-tact rip tag the still looks brand new and unwashed that I haven't worn these more than a few times. I brought them, my receipt and the cardboard hang tag into the store to exchange them given that these are clearly defective. However, the associate refused stating that the only thing they can do is have their tailor sew the hole.
If the hole was along a seam, I can understand the offered resolution. However when the hole isn't along a seam, a see fix is going to create a small bulge. Even though I am part of the old R & D and purchased these at a discount, the performance and quality of these tights is unacceptable given the price point.
My lululemon purchases and positive feedback to others has greatly diminished over the past year mainly due to quality. Generally I've had positive experiences with lululemon standing behind their gear. Unfortunately this latest incident has finally driven me away from lululemon.
By the way, the associate did say that if I found the stitching uncomfortable, they'd take them back. I surmise that Lululemon doesn't value my time in that I have to wait for these to be stitched, pick them up in store, then wear and wash them. Then, return to the the store, hope that they stand by their word. Or, was I suppose to lie in the first place and say that the stitching bothered me, and by the way, there's a hole??

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Full-On Luxtreme 28"
column5: HAAAAAATE The Hi-Rise, Fit Okay Otherwise
column6:
These pants are better than similar alternatives from other brands (specifically the under armour, which are similar material and only cost $59, but slide down just from walking and I ended up donating after wearing for a frustrating 2 months). The main body of these tights fit well and for the most part stay put. They are close to being perfect, but there are a few flaws that keep them from being as comfortable and useful as they should be.
First, the picture of the model for these Hi-Rise pants make it appear that the waist goes up to your bellybutton...maybe if you're 6' tall. But I am only 5'4" and the waist reaches over my rib cage and to the bottom of my bra line. It looks absolutely ridiculous!!! It's even too much for the trendy "high pants" look where people wear high rise "mom" pants with a tube top (or sports bra). There is very little skin showing between my pants and my bra (I hate that look anyway but thought maybe that's why they made these?).
The only benefit of a waist this high is during winter when it adds an extra layer of warmth over your body. The waist is tight around my rib cage, but if I do certain workouts, the waist starts to slip down over the narrower part of my waist, at which point it makes wrinkly bunched up rolls under my shirt where I would otherwise have a completely flat and tight stomach. The high waist might be good for people who have a pudgy belly and are hoping to smooth it out, but if you are in good shape, it actually has the opposite effect.
The Luxtreme material is better than the Luon for keeping the pants from pilling, but the Luxtreme is a little less sturdy than the Luon (because they are a thinner material and they have a tighter fit). You have to put them on kind of like pantyhose, and you have to be careful not to dig your nails in too much and poke a hole in them if you have long nails.
The Luxtreme also gives less of a "smoothing" effect over butt dimples than the Luon. If you have a fairly nice backside, it won't make much difference, but if you have more dimples it will be more noticeable in the Luxtreme than the Luon. The Luxtreme is more comfortable in all weather because it keeps you warm and covered up in the cold, but cool in the warmer weather, whereas Luon will keep you warm all the time, and is too hot in warmer weather.
The length of these pants is a bit long for my 5 feet 4 inches, but they just bunch a small amount at the ankles and I think they look good. I tried the 7/8th pants but those just ended up looking like I was wearing pants that were too small, more like high waters. Also, I wear a size 6 in wunder unders and I am 120 pounds, but have worn them when I was only 110 pounds also, and they fit perfectly for both weights (I am for the most part the same size at both weights, I just have more muscle at the higher weight so that might be why). Size 4 fits, but is just small enough that it creates a bit of a squeezed sausage look in my butt and thighs, but in the 6 I look toned and strong. I wear a 4 in their shorts though, so I guess the size difference is my thighs. Hope that helps someone figure out their size.
Lastly, because the Luxtreme is a more sleek material than Luon, they will eventually slide down a bit when doing more intense workouts, where Luon never does that. I have tested these in several situations before reviewing and have done an hour cycling class, a body pump (weight lifting) class, and gone for a 3 mile, a 5 mile and an 8 mile run in them as well as spent a whole day running errands. They stay put for the cycling, body pump and 3 mile run, but once you get to the longer runs, they do start to slide a little bit, and when the run is over (or during the run), you will find yourself cinching them back up because they are falling in the crotch area a bit. I have a well defined backside, which is better for these pants because your butt will hold up the pants better than if you have a smaller, flatter behind where there's nothing to hold the pants in place over your waist. I have 2 pairs of wunder unders in Luon and they never ever slip or slide, even on a 10 mile run.
All that being said, I would recommend the Luxtreme over the Luon because they will look new longer, and for me, I want these to last several years because of how expensive they are. I don't want to replace my $100 pants every year. But keep in mind that you have to be more careful with them so you don't get holes in them. I have 17 pairs of Lulu pants (5 wunder under and 12 other) and 5 pairs of shorts that I have purchased over the last 10 years. The quality of the pants has gone down over the years, as my 10 year old pants (while not stylish anymore) have held up better and look newer than my 2 year old pants (that really need to be thrown out because I have to take a sweater de-baller to them almost every time I wear them and they are faded and look old and worn out). I also have these tights in the "low rise," which aren't much better, since the waist on those looks like the picture for the "hi-rise" (the waist goes up to the belly button). My 10 year old low rise Lulus hit right at the hip bone and are true low rise. I wish they'd go back to those, if so these would be perfect running pants.
